  "text": "Previous attempts at developing gene therapeutics to treat wet AMD have used sFLT-1-based constructs as well. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] An Australian group inserted a natural form of sFLT-1 [CITATION_3] under the control of a CMV promoter into a rAAV2 delivery vehicle (rAAV2.sFLT-1) that was administered via subretinal injection. [CITATION_4] Structurally very similar to rAAV2-sVEGFRv-1, rAAV2.sFLT-1 completed phase I clinical trials, [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] but was no longer pursued after phase II clinical trials indicated that rAAV2.sFLT-1 treatment did not result in significant visual gain. [CITATION_7] A separate group based in the United States utilized intravitreal injections as the treatment paradigm to deliver a",
